Based on your structure:

```text
src/main/resources/
└── db/
    └── changelog/
        ├── master.yaml
        ├── data/
        │   └── as400-users.csv
        └── v007/
            └── v007-as400-user-import.yaml
```

use the following paths.

## `master.yaml`

Because `master.yaml` and the `v007` directory are both inside `db/changelog`:

```yaml
databaseChangeLog:
  - include:
      file: v007/v007-as400-user-import.yaml
      relativeToChangelogFile: true
```

## `v007/v007-as400-user-import.yaml`

The YAML file is inside `v007`, while the CSV is inside the sibling `data` directory. Therefore, go up one directory and then into `data`:

```yaml
databaseChangeLog:

  - changeSet:
      id: v007-01-create-as400-user-staging
      author: partner-repository
      changes:
        - createTable:
            tableName: as400_user_import_staging
            columns:
              - column:
                  name: entity
                  type: varchar(50)

              - column:
                  name: source_record_type
                  type: varchar(50)

              - column:
                  name: related_parent
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: source_personal_id
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: gps_group_number
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: source_point_of_sales_id
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: first_name
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: surname
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: email
                  type: varchar(255)

              - column:
                  name: phone_number
                  type: varchar(50)

              - column:
                  name: language
                  type: varchar(10)

              - column:
                  name: user_status
                  type: varchar(20)

              - column:
                  name: sales_point_id
                  type: varchar(100)

              - column:
                  name: sales_point_name
                  type: varchar(255)

              - column:
                  name: relationship_type
                  type: varchar(50)

              - column:
                  name: relationship_status
                  type: varchar(20)

              - column:
                  name: imported_at
                  type: timestamp with time zone
                  defaultValueComputed: CURRENT_TIMESTAMP

      rollback:
        - dropTable:
            tableName: as400_user_import_staging


  - changeSet:
      id: v007-02-load-as400-user-csv
      author: partner-repository
      changes:
        - loadData:
            file: ../data/as400-users.csv
            relativeToChangelogFile: true
            tableName: as400_user_import_staging
            encoding: UTF-8
            separator: ","
            quotchar: '"'
            usePreparedStatements: true
            columns:
              - column:
                  header: entity
                  name: entity
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: source_record_type
                  name: source_record_type
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: related_parent
                  name: related_parent
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: source_personal_id
                  name: source_personal_id
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: gps_group_number
                  name: gps_group_number
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: source_point_of_sales_id
                  name: source_point_of_sales_id
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: first_name
                  name: first_name
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: surname
                  name: surname
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: email
                  name: email
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: phone_number
                  name: phone_number
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: language
                  name: language
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: user_status
                  name: user_status
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: sales_point_id
                  name: sales_point_id
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: sales_point_name
                  name: sales_point_name
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: relationship_type
                  name: relationship_type
                  type: STRING

              - column:
                  header: relationship_status
                  name: relationship_status
                  type: STRING
```

The important path is:

```yaml
file: ../data/as400-users.csv
```

It is resolved like this:

```text
db/changelog/v007
        ↓ ..
db/changelog
        ↓ data
db/changelog/data/as400-users.csv
```

You could also reference the CSV from the classpath root:

```yaml
file: db/changelog/data/as400-users.csv
relativeToChangelogFile: false
```

However, for your folder structure, this is cleaner:

```yaml
file: ../data/as400-users.csv
relativeToChangelogFile: true
```

Also ensure Spring points to the master file:

```yaml
spring:
  liquibase:
    change-log: classpath:db/changelog/master.yaml
```
